UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Jaime LUJAN-ALCALA, Defendant-Appellant. No. 10-50199. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. April 18, 2011. Paul A. Barr, Federal Defenders Of San Diego, Inc., San Diego, CA, for Defendant-Appellant. Fred Sheppard, Office of the U.S. Attorney, San Diego, CA, for Plaintiff-Appellee.

Before: HAWKINS and FISHER, Circuit Judges, and WOLF, Chief District Judge.*

The Honorable Mark L. Wolf, Chief United States District Judge for the District of Massachusetts, sitting by designation.

ORDER

The Government’s Unopposed Motion to Unseal Memorandum Disposition is GRANTED.
